Her father, Anil Kapoor, is also reportedly 'obsessed' with grandson Vayu.

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: GE Aerospace delivered the fourth F404-IN20 engine to HAL for India's Tejas Mk1A. HAL confirmed negotiations concluded for a follow-on order of 113 F404 engines, valued over $1 billion, expected to be signed in October. This deal, alongside F414 tech transfer talks, significantly boosts India's defence indigenisation efforts.
title: Boost for Tejas fleet: HAL receives 4th GE engine; $1 bn follow-on order likely in Oct

title: 'Example of sacrifice, selfless service': PM Modi hails RSS' 100-year journey

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The US government has entered its first shutdown since 2019, fueled by a bitter healthcare funding clash between President Trump and Democrats. Unlike previous standoffs, the administration is threatening permanent federal job cuts to reshape the workforce, sparking widespread anger.
title: First since 2019: US govt shuts down – Why it’s more serious this time

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Former India cricketer Aakash Chopra advised against preparing rank turner pitches for the upcoming Test series against West Indies, warning they could be counterproductive by reducing the competitive gap. He advocated for balanced surfaces that allow matches to progress naturally over four to five days, noting how extreme pitches have negatively impacted senior Indian batsmen's confidence and performance.

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi endorsed US President Donald Trump's 20-point Gaza peace plan, hailing it as a viable path to lasting stability for Palestinian and Israeli people. Trump, alongside Israeli PM Netanyahu, unveiled the initiative, proposing an immediate ceasefire and hostage release.

description: Three special teams have been formed to arrest TVK general secretary Bussy Anand and deputy general secretary CTR Nirmal Kumar following a stampede at a rally that killed 41. Police accuse them of mismanagement and deliberate delays, while the two leaders have sought anticipatory bail from the Madras High Court.

description: Indiana Fever star Kelsey Mitchell suffered a leg injury in Game 5 of the WNBA semifinals against the Las Vegas Aces, exiting the game in the third quarter. This critical blow leaves the already injury-riddled Fever without their leading scorer and MVP finalist, severely impacting their championship aspirations. Her condition and return timeline remain uncertain.

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge was admitted to MS Ramaiah Hospital in Bengaluru for a planned pacemaker implantation and is reported stable. The 83-year-old leader, who was earlier hospitalized for fever, is scheduled to address a public rally in Kohima, Nagaland, on October 7, focusing on youth employment and good governance.

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Nick Geoppo, who lost 110 pounds and kept it off for six years, reveals the weight loss industry's unsustainable cycle. He advocates aiming to conquer obesity permanently, not just lose weight, through a 'common sense diet.' What is a common sense diet? Well it as interesting as it sounds. The man claims its sustainable and helped him in his journey. "Your goal is not to lose weight," he said. Read more.

description: Indian stock markets will remain closed on October 2 for Gandhi Jayanti and Dussehra, with trading resuming Friday. October features 11 market holidays, including key Diwali dates. description: Student suicides in India have surged by 65% over the past decade, significantly outpacing the national average and raising urgent concerns about mental health. Academic pressure, unemployment fears, and inadequate support systems are key factors. Targeted interventions in educational institutions, along with comprehensive mental health support, are crucial to address this alarming trend.

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: RBI Governor Sanjay Malhotra warned that US tariffs pose risks to India's economic growth, potentially decelerating it from late 2025. description: It is likely that the team management would want to play on turning pitches when South Africa come to play two Tests in Nov. description: Delhi is the country's crime capital with 1508.9 IPC cases per lakh population, while Jharkhand reports the fewest. description: Climate activist Sonam Wangchuk's wife, Gitanjali Angmo, vehemently condemned "blatant lies" and "baseless" anti-national narratives against him.
